latest_report.diagnosis: Wi-Fi performance is adequate but affected by random dropouts, likely due to network congestion and interference.

performance.interpretation: Current download speeds are close to the ISP plan, but upload speeds are below expectations. The ping time is reasonable but could be optimized further.

problems: Random dropouts likely caused by network congestion and interference from nearby networks.
High congestion on 2.4GHz band with three networks on channel 1 and one on 6.
Multiple strong signals on the 5GHz band could cause interference.
Inadequate placement of router may limit coverage.
fixes: Change the 2.4GHz channel to 6 to avoid interference from channels 1 and 11.
Shift the 5GHz channel to 149 to minimize congestion caused by other networks on 36.
Consider relocating the router to a more central location in the home to enhance coverage.
Enable Smart Connect to optimize device connections between 2.4GHz and 5GHz bands.
Regularly monitor and adjust channels to adapt to network changes and congestion.
